                                                    EB pull up trio

      A STAFF REPORTER
      Subrata Bhattacharya 
             
	Calcutta: East Bengal on Friday cracked the whip on indisciplined players as pressure mounted on coach Subrata Bhattacharya in the wake of the teams prolonged dismal run in the I-League. 
    
	Defender M. Suresh, along with medios Chandan Das and McDonald Mukansi have been charged with anti-club activity and asked to explain their conduct. 
    
	These three players have been found guilty on grounds of indiscipline and have been showcaused, secretary Santosh Bhattacharya said after a meeting at the club tent. 
    
	Mukansi, in fact, had a closed door meeting with the coach where the South African was told to buck up and maintain discipline, according to a source. Former captain Alvito DCunha, whose conduct has also been a talking point in the past few weeks, escaped punishment. 
    
	The officials expressed concern over the teams showing and feared that it could affect the sponsors interest in the team. The officials were learnt to have kept faith in Subrata till the end of the I-League, which is halfway through. Mukansi and Chandan have, however, been included in the Ludhiana-bound squad for the 10th-round match against JCT. Suresh, who is nursing a knee injury, will stay back. 
    
	East Bengal are currently in eighth position with eight points  ahead of Air India and Salgaocar. 
                                                   
